Compiler's comment: During the CSEWG 2018 meeting Dr.
Ramirez (U. Kentucky) raised issues about this entry,
please see page 6 of his presentation:
https://indico.bnl.gov/event/5067/contributions/24819
/attachments /20668/27769/CSWEG2018 ramirez.pdf. From
Ramirez: "I have also attached the Knox et al.
NP/A 378, 503 (1982) paper where they mentioned that
the Legendre coefficients they used are in CM system
while En are in the lab system. When I tried to extract
the Legendre coefficients using Perey's inelastic data
as given by EXFOR, I was able to reproduce those
presented in the Knox's paper found in Fig. 2."
NNDC was able to locate the Perey's paper,
NSR keynumber 1971PEYZ; that is an abstract of the ANS
meeting without any details.

Measurements were made relative to hydrogen
scattering. Below 7.33% the sum of the integrated
elastic and inelastic cross sections had an average
systematic difference of 4% compared to ENDF/B-IV
total cross sections. All data was thus renormalized
